\f0\i\b\fs24 \cf2 Branding\
\b0 Logo and header branding for the system.\ \
\b Navigation\
\b0 If necessary, we will include mobile ready navigation.\ \
\b Create New \
\b0 Create a new Element, Metadata Template or Runtime instance. \ \
\b Recent\
\b0 Shows the three most recent Elements, Metadata Templates and Runs. \ \
\b See All\
\b0 This will bring up a grid showing all Elements; Metadata Templates; or Runtimes. This will be mocked up upon approval by CEDAR.\ \
\b Edit/Delete\
\b0 Edit or delete an Element, Metadata Template or runtime.}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1347\cocoasubrtf570 {\fonttbl\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Georgia;} {\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;\red111\green111\blue111;} \pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\slleading120\pardirnatural
\f0\i\b\fs24 \cf2 Element Name\
\b0 Enter the Element Name here. This will show up on the Dashboard and in the Metadata Template Creator.\ \ UI Note: Fields will use Float Labels (shown next to these annotations). Once a field has focus (the user has clicked into them, the field text animates from the field to the header location. \ \
\b Element Description\
\b0 Enter the Element Description here. This will show up on the Dashboard and in the Metadata Template Creator.\ \
\b Add Item\
\b0 Add form elements and data capture fields from this clickable list.\ \
\b Add Item Field\
\b0 Visual cue that an Item should be added to this Element.\ \
\b Item Name, Help Text, Preview\
\b0 The name will be shown in some contexts, as will help text. This also shows the text box preview.\ \
\b Required\
\b0 Toggle whether this Item is required.\ \
\b Advanced\
\b0 Clicking this will bring up the accordion panel with advanced options included.\ \
\b Add\
\b0 Add this item. Note the rollover effect shown next to these annotations.\ \
\b Delete\
\b0 Delete this item. Note the rollover effect shown next to these annotations.\ \
\b Add Item\
\b0 Visual cue that the user can add additional Items to complete this Element.\ \
\b Done\
\b0 Saves the Element and returns the user to the Dashboard.\ \
\b Advanced\
\b0 This needs further discussion, but in general, clicking on advanced brings up additional options for each Item. We need definition for each of these. \ \
\b Preview\
\b0 This shows how the item will look on the screen and offers controls to show Help Text, edit the Item or delete the Item.}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1347\cocoasubrtf570 {\fonttbl\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Georgia;} {\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;\red111\green111\blue111;} \pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\slleading120\pardirnatural
\f0\i\b\fs24 \cf2 Template Name\
\b0 Enter the Template Name here. This will show up on the Dashboard and in the Metadata Template Runtime.\ \
\b Template Description\
\b0 Enter the Template Description here. This will show up on the Dashboard and in the Metadata Template Runtime.\ \
\b Add Element\
\b0 This will list all Elements available for this Template.\ \
\b New Element\
\b0 In the case that a user needs an Element not yet created, this adds an easy button to get into the Element creator interface. \ \
\b Add Element\
\b0 A visual cue for the user to add an Element to the template.\ \
\b Preview\
\b0 This shows the Element in the template layout. Users can view Help Text, edit or delete the Element.\ \
\b Done\
\b0 Clicking Done will bring the user back to the Dashboard. \ \ Note: Ideally this template will be getting saved as each Element is added, eliminating the chance for loss of work. \ }

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1347\cocoasubrtf570 {\fonttbl\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Georgia;} {\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;\red111\green111\blue111;} \pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\slleading120\pardirnatural
\f0\i\b\fs24 \cf2 Run a Metadata Template\
\b0 A list of templates to choose from to run. Clicking one of these loads the template in the right column.\ \
\b New Metadata Template\
\b0 In the case that the user needs a new template not listed, this button brings them directly to the Metadata Template Creator to easily build a new one.\ \
\b Back to Dashboard\
\b0 Brings the user back to the Dashboard. This is necessary because a user can run as many templates as they would like from this screen, so they need a way to get back to the starting point of the system.\ \
\b Template Fields\
\b0 This shows the Elements created in Metadata Template Creator, along with icon cues that data has been correctly entered. \ \
\b Help Text Icon\
\b0 This can be clicked on for help text and once data has been correctly entered can change to the success icon.\ \
\b Error\
\b0 Shows the data error icon and gives a reason for the error as well as steps to correct it.\ \
\b Run\
\b0 Runs the template. After a successful run, the page will show a success screen, and the user can choose another Metadata Template to run.\ \
\b Cancel\
\b0 Cancels this Metadata Template, removes it from the screen and allows a user to select a new one.}
